{
  "stem": "23090.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So growing up under these conditions was a-- was a daily chore to each of us-- I mean, from the youngest to the ones that could walk and, and understand, like I was beginning to, to the zaydes, to the grown people.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you just grow into it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's all I can say on, on, on, on pre-- pre-invasion or pre-occupation.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Since I was not in the army, since I was not privy to any of the-- what an adult could and would participate in, I was just a young bystander, as a child, but I formed my own-- my own way of coping with it.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Any child, I think, does-- here, any place else.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You sort of form your own, and you do your own little way, and you cope with it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You sort of-- it's like a young boy getting another brother or sister, or a sister getting a brother.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Somehow, they just cope with it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's, it's not a good thing, and nothing that the parents or anyone can say to them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They have to sort of work it with them-- themselves.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and this is what happens under bad and terrible conditions, not just for me, but for any young child under any extenuating circumstances.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They form their own life, their, their way of coping with it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was scared all the time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was just-- was just, just scared.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, you hear these things flying and bombing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And every time that happens, your mother grabs you, and she runs into that room.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And under the window, that was your best place, is right under the window.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because that way if anything collapsed, it collapses in the middle of the room rather than at that end.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then you were worried about glass.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
